Under the arm a portfolio with three new leases to three flats: for his own and the flats of his daughters and his son, who is serving a prison sentence.
All three of them have just been increased in rent under the so-called "deregulation".
Instead of 3500 kroner monthly rent, the son is to be able to cover next year for a 2 bedroom apartment with kitchen of the second category 4100 kroner.
"And there's not even running hot water in the apartment and you have to heat in a simple coal oven," he says with his finger on the son's new lease, for whose signature he has a power of attorney.
"But what - I signed," he explains half-disturbed and half-resigned.
