This is paid by corporations like Monsanto, Nestle or Bayer.
Kuiper had played a significant role in the Efsa test regulations for gene plants and was thus in a clear conflict of interest, criticisms Then.
The Efsa regulations are identical in terms of terms with the position papers of the Ilsi and thus bear the signature of the industry, which is actually to be controlled by the authority in the Italian Parma.
It is already the second time that Testbiotech is calling for a conflict of interests.
For example, a high-ranking Efsa manager was recently without any conditions or transitional period to the Swiss agricultural group Syngenta - and had thus changed sides.
The Mitteldeutsche Rundfunk (MDR) had also recently revealed human relations between the controlling EU authority and industrial lobby, which the Federal Environment Agency as well as EU Parliamentarians have heard.
However, the Efsa cannot detect any conflict of interest.
All the serious data, including those of industry, should be taken back as long as they are of high technical quality, is stated in an opinion.
