"We want to know, for example, what genetically modified maize does in the field," says Then.
Current practice is to test only isolated proteins, but not the entire gene plant, which does not provide reliable results.
"If you don't look for the risks, how can you find them?"Then asks accusingly.
Angelika Hilbeck sees that as well.
The scientist has been researching genetic engineering since 1994 and is currently working at the Technical University of Zurich.
In this field, as in the US, industry is now increasingly trying to influence or discredit critical scientists in Europe.
