Prior to the disaster that killed eleven workers and led to the biggest environmental disaster in the United States, President Barack Obama, under pressure from the opposition and industry, had signalled his willingness to allow new drilling in the eastern part of the Gulf of Mexico.
The proponents want to reduce the US' dependence on oil supplies from abroad.
