In October, Minister of the Interior Ken Salazar had lifted the post-explosion drill stop.
Subsequently, various oil companies had immediately submitted applications for new drilling projects.
With stricter controls and stricter security regulations, Obama and Salazar want to rule out a new catastrophe.
At present, the competent supervisory authority, which was in disrepute after numerous charges of corruption, is being fundamentally reformed.
In parallel, Obama has announced to close lucrative tax loopholes for oil and gas companies.
