This computer science program called PLM was used for the development of assembly chains in factories around the world, energy plants and high-precision instruments.
The aim is a faithful reproduction or simulation of a product or process before it is actually built to avoid errors and unnecessary costs.
PLM has facilitated the development of cameras of Canon, the planes of Sukhoi and the most famous commercial vehicles of Nissan.
