Today, 180 highly qualified young people are employed in Red Bull's team. They carry out analyses and all possible changes to the racing car with powerful computer systems.
Siemens Manager explained that PLM software is capable of analyzing and improving all components of Red Bull racing cars, except the engine for which Renault is solely responsible.
The materials, the fuel, the aerodynamics and the safety elements are changed.
The changes can be transferred from the virtual reality of the simulator to reality within less than 24 hours thanks to advanced production facilities and high-tech autoclaves.
