The US changes the rules for obtaining a visa
Persons must present themselves to the visa application service points before talking to the consulate, thus reducing the costs of waiting.
As of 10 January 2011, the procedures for applying for a visa will change at the United States Embassy and Consulates.
In the new procedure, most applicants will have to present themselves to the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English) before talking to the consulate.
The staff of the ASC shall record the biometric data of the applicant, which shall be verified by the Consulate prior to the interview.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of the visa is reduced, as it is no longer necessary to pay separately for the appointment, processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the return to 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who only want to extend their visa do not need to have a conversation at the consulate, they only have to imagine at the nearest ASC where they will present their documents and take their fingerprints.
Since the biometric data are collected in the ASC, applicants who require a second appointment in the consulate will be left with less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa at the consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo do not have to pay the service surcharge of 26 dollars.
Further information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
