It is obvious that in the future the states will not place any more reserved information online - that would be like a hanging on the street corner.
But it is equally obvious that it is in vain with the current technologies to hope to keep confidential reports on the phone secret.
Nothing is easier than to find out if and when a head of state moved on a plane and contacted one of his colleagues.
How could private relationships be maintained in the future and only for certain ears?
