In the tap water, the analyses have exposed the presence of nitrates and chloroform.
At dinner, the salmon steak with 34 determined chemical residues was "most abundant", and even the plastic plate used to warm up the meal in the microwave was not unloaded.
The final risk of this "pollutant cocktail" for the consumer "is likely to be undervalued," the study says.
The Alliance Europe Ecologie-Les Verts (EE-LV) has, for its part, proposed "in view of the urgency of the situation" to introduce a moratorium on the use of pesticides to stop the "increase in civilisation".
In July, a study by the European Food Safety Authority (EFSA) identified 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables that are consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
